cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on dependency parsing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also extensively discusses the use of multilingual contextual word representations (CWRs), which are a type of deep learning model commonly used in NLP. Therefore, categories related to deep learning such as cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of simulated scenarios and the analysis of language models, which could fall under categories such as cs.NE (simulation and modeling) and cs.CV (computer vision, which often involves analyzing learned representations).
